channel.title: Internet explorers [solved]
channel.description:
Isn't a hardware question but it is technical. I run windows 7 and only use firefox to browse the internet.
Recently in task manager I've seen iexplorer.exe running. In fact 4 of them are running right now taking up between 10,000K to 50,000K worth of memory each.
I wasn't really worried about this until I looked in the windows 7 volume mixer which lets you change the volume of individual applications, and it shows that I've got 4 internet explorer applications running.
So is this a virus? If so what should I do about it, and what is the virus doing?
Ty

item.title: Internet explorers [solved]
item.dc:creator: @davidude36 Brolapse
item.description:
@davidude36 wrote:

eczema3:

What happens when you end the process(es) in task manager? Do they come back? Does something in your system screw up? Nothing?

They come straight back on.

edit - lawl suggested i use process explorer

docs.microsoft.com

Process Explorer - Windows Sysinternals

Find out what files, registry keys and other objects processes have open, which DLLs they have loaded, and more.


using that found that the iexplorer.exe’s were trying to access an activation server for guitar pro.
